text.tspan: Prevalence of alcohol use disorders by age, World, 1990 to 2019
Share of the population within particular age categories suffering from alcohol use disorders. Alcohol dependence is
defined by the International Classification of Diseases as the presence of three or more indicators of dependence
for at least a month within the previous year.
Data source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease (2019)
